@c7abe @QwikDev 1. Resumable execution model (no hydration)
2. Qwik optimizer (shreds files to be reduced down to minimum code needed, which you could call a "custom bundler" in a sense)
3. Fancy serialization of the signal graph to know how to update the UI w/o the component code

@solid_js is in between - never logging on click, but does do one log for hydration in the browser

Granted, Qwik falls back to a vdom diff for certain more complex cases

Whereas Solid never does in any situation, and is a big inspiration we are working incrementally toward https://t.co/OiaLERdh07

